Document: VisualInstance3D
Path: godot/classes/class_visualinstance3d.rst
Summary: Base class for all 3D nodes that have a visual representation.

Inherits: GeometryInstance3D < Node3D < Spatial < Node

VisualInstance3D is the base class for all 3D nodes that have a visual representation. This includes nodes like MeshInstance3D, Sprite3D, and Camera3D. It provides common properties and methods for all visual objects in a 3D scene, such as visibility, rendering layers, and material overrides.

Key Rule: VisualInstance3D itself cannot be directly added to a scene. It serves as an abstract base class for other visual node types.
